{
  "texts": [
    "The EEG signals were sampled at 512 Hz and then downsampled to 128 Hz while removing electrooculography (EOG) artifacts for pre-processing.",
    "In our experiments, only the 32-channel EEG data was used for classification.",
    "Therefore, the dimension of total EEG data is 32 × 40 × 32 × 8064 (#participants × #trials × #channels × temporal length).",
    "After watching the music video, each participant was asked to report their emotion in levels of arousal, valence, liking, and dominance from 1 to 9.",
    "Among them, arousal ranges from inactive (e.g., uninterested, bored) to active (e.g., alert, excited), while valence ranges from unpleasant (e.g., sad, stressed) to pleasant (e.g., happy, elated)."
  ]
}